    "department": "Legal",
    "description": "WHY HARVEY\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate — not incrementally, but end-to-end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come.\n\nThis is a rare chance to help build a generational company at a true inflection point. With 1000+ customers in 60+ countries, strong product-market fit, and world-class investor support, we’re scaling fast and defining a new category in real time. The work is ambitious, the bar is high, and the opportunity for growth — personal, professional, and financial — is unmatched.\n\nOur team is sharp, motivated, and deeply committed to the mission. We move fast, operate with intensity, and take real ownership of the problems we tackle — from early thinking to long-term outcomes. We stay close to our customers — from leadership to engineers — and work together to solve real problems with urgency and care. If you thrive in ambiguity, push for excellence, and want to help shape the future of work alongside others who raise the bar, we invite you to build with us.\n\nAt Harvey, the future of professional services is being written today — and we’re just getting started.\n\n\n\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nReporting to the Lead Corporate Paralegal, you will serve as the primary governance lead for Harvey’s EMEA and APAC entities.\n\nYou will own and manage corporate lifecycle matters across multiple jurisdictions, ensuring compliance with local statutory and governance requirements. This role requires direct coordination with internal leadership, external directors, outside counsel, and cross-functional stakeholders across time zones.\n\nYou will play a critical role in strengthening Harvey’s global governance infrastructure as the company continues to scale rapidly.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Own governance and compliance oversight for Harvey’s EMEA and APAC subsidiary portfolio, ensuring adherence to local statutory and regulatory requirements.\n\n - Lead full entity lifecycle management, including incorporations, restructurings, post-acquisition integrations, and dissolutions.\n\n - Proactively manage global governance calendars and statutory obligations, partnering with Finance, Tax, and external advisors to oversee annual accounts and required filings.\n\n - Coordinate and lead board, shareholder, and committee meetings, including agenda development, board materials preparation, and direct engagement with internal and external directors.\n\n - Draft and finalize corporate documentation, including minutes, written resolutions, secretary certificates, and related governance records.\n\n - Design and implement scalable governance processes and controls, while supporting high-impact legal and cross-functional initiatives tied to Harvey’s global growth.\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n\n - Paralegal certificate and/or Bachelor’s degree.\n\n - 5+ years of corporate paralegal experience in a law firm or multinational in-house environment.\n\n - Significant experience managing non-US subsidiaries and multi-jurisdictional compliance.\n\n - Strong knowledge of global corporate governance frameworks.\n\n - Demonstrated ability to independently manage governance workflows and statutory obligations.\n\n - Experience interacting with directors and senior stakeholders.\n\n - Exceptional organizational rigor and attention to detail.\n\n - Strong written and verbal communication skills.\n\n\nDEPENDING ON YOUR LOCATION, AN APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICE MAY APPLY TO YOU. YOU CAN FIND ALL OF OUR APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICES [HERE https://www.notion.so/harveyai/Harvey-Candidate-Privacy-Policies-319ac3fcdd7a803bb807d5094f249922].\n\n#LI-LM1\n\nHarvey is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made by emailing accommodations@harvey.ai",
